(32, 1, '2014-02-01 14:35:05', '2014-02-01 13:35:05', '<!--:en-->The “Plandište 1” wind park is located in the northeast of Serbia, in Southern Banat, well known for the strong wind called “Košava”. The main direction of the Košave is southeast – northwest. The average wind velocity on the location (at the level of 125 m) is above 6.5 m/s, with minimum turbulence intensity.\r\n\r\nThe unevenness of the grounds is such that it is very favorable for using the wind energy. The measurement of wind characteristics has been performed on the site on a 125 m high weather pole for several years. The pole is furnished with highest class sensor, placed at the respective heights. The measurements have been performed since April 2011.\r\n\r\nThe GMAO MERRA (Global Modeling and Assimilation Office of the NASA Centre for Climate Simulation – The Modern Era Retrospective-analysis for Research and Applications) data were used for the long-term correlation of wind related data.\r\n\r\nThe wind potential analyses and the annual return for various producers and models of wind turbines were prepared by two independent globally recognized consulting companies (DEWI and Anemos GmbH).<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Opis projekta - Analiza potencijala vetra<!--:--><!--:en-->Project description - Analysis of the wind potential<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'opis-projekta-analiza-potencijala-vetra', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:31:07', '2014-02-01 16:31:07', '', 0, 'http://nemanja-pc/?page_id=32', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(33, 1, '2014-02-01 14:35:05', '2014-02-01 13:35:05', '<!--:SR--><h1></h1><!--:--><!--:en--><h1>Project description - Analysis of the wind potential</h1>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h5>The “Plandište 1” wind park is located in the northeast of Serbia, in Southern Banat, well known for the strong wind called “Košava”. The main direction of the Košave is southeast – northwest. The average wind velocity on the location (at the level of 125 m) is above 6.5 m/s, with minimum turbulence intensity.\r\n\r\nThe unevenness of the grounds is such that it is very favorable for using the wind energy. The measurement of wind characteristics has been performed on the site on a 125 m high weather pole for several years. The pole is furnished with highest class sensor, placed at the respective heights. The measurements have been performed since April 2011.\r\n\r\nThe GMAO MERRA (Global Modeling and Assimilation Office of the NASA Centre for Climate Simulation – The Modern Era Retrospective-analysis for Research and Applications) data were used for the long-term correlation of wind related data.\r\n\r\nThe wind potential analyses and the annual return for various producers and models of wind turbines were prepared by two independent globally recognized consulting companies (DEWI and Anemos GmbH).</h5>\r\n</div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Opis projekta - Analiza potencijala vetra<!--:--><!--:en-->Project description - Analysis of the wind potential<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 14:35:05', '2014-02-01 13:35:05', '', 32, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=33', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2014-02-01 14:36:02', '2014-02-01 13:36:02', '<!--:SR-->Temelji zaštite životne sredine baziraju se na:\r\n\r\n1) Očuvanju pejzaža, biljnog pokrivača i obradivih površina;\r\n2) Očuvanju voda za piće, površinskih i podzemnih voda;\r\n3) Očuvanju atmosfere;\r\n4) Očuvanju zemljišta;\r\n5) Zaštita od buke, vibracija i zračenja;\r\n6) Zaštita od udesa.<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->ZAŠTITA ŽIVOTNE SREDINE<!--:--><!--:en-->ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'zastita-zivotne-sredine', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:34:19', '2014-02-01 16:34:19', '', 0, 'http://nemanja-pc/?page_id=34', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(35, 1, '2014-02-01 14:36:02', '2014-02-01 13:36:02', '<!--:SR--><h1>ZAŠTITA ŽIVOTNE SREDINE</h1>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h5>Temelji zaštite životne sredine baziraju se na:\r\n\r\n1) Očuvanju pejzaža, biljnog pokrivača i obradivih površina;\r\n2) Očuvanju voda za piće, površinskih i podzemnih voda;\r\n3) Očuvanju atmosfere;\r\n4) Očuvanju zemljišta;\r\n5) Zaštita od buke, vibracija i zračenja;\r\n6) Zaštita od udesa.</h5>\r\n</div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->ZAŠTITA ŽIVOTNE SREDINE<!--:--><!--:en-->ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '34-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 14:36:02', '2014-02-01 13:36:02', '', 34, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=35', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(36, 1, '2014-02-01 14:36:44', '2014-02-01 13:36:44', '<!--:SR-->Ukupno smanjenje emisije CO2 tokom 20 godina, koji se odnosi na projektovani radni vek vetroelektrane iznosio bi 5,4 miliona tona CO2. Proračun smanjenja emisije CO2 urađen je prema primenjivoj metodologiji za ocenu projekta mehanizma čistog razvoja (CDM).\r\n\r\nTipično putničko vozilo emituje oko 5,1 tonu CO2 godišnje. Doprinos iz zelene energije dobijene iz vetra u vetroelektrani „Plandište 1“ bi bila ekvivalentna ukljanjanju 53 000 automobila sa ulica svake godine.\r\n\r\nProjekat vetroelektrana „Plandište 1“ odobren je kao projekat Mehanizma čistog razvoja od Nacionalnog tela za sproveđenje projekata mehanizama čistog razvoja, Ministarstvo životne sredine, rudarstva i prostornog planiranja.\r\n\r\nTakođe, projekat je prihvaćen kao projekat mehanizma čistog razvoja od strane Konferencije država ugovornica okvirne konvencije ujedinjenih nacija o promeni klime</h5>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a><!--:--><!--:en-->The total reduction of CO2 emission over 20 years, related to the projected life of the wind parks would be 5.4 million tons of CO2. The calculation of reduction of CO2 emission was made according to the applicable methodology for assessment of the clean development mechanism (CDM) project.\r\n\r\nA typical passenger vehicle emits about 5.1 ton of CO2 annually. The contribution from green energy obtained from the wind at the “Plandište 1“ wind park would be equivalent to removal of 53 000 cars from the street every year.\r\n\r\nThe “Plandište 1“ wind park was approved as a Clean Development Mechanism project by the National Authority for the implementation of clean development mechanism project, Ministry of Environment, Mining and Spatial Planning.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the project was approved as a clean development mechanism project by the Conference of Parties on United National Framework Convention on Climate Change\r\n\r\n<a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->CDM, CO2<!--:--><!--:en-->CDM, CO2<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cdm-co2', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:25:48', '2014-02-01 16:25:48', '', 0, 'http://nemanja-pc/?page_id=36', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(37, 1, '2014-02-01 14:36:44', '2014-02-01 13:36:44', '<!--:SR--><h1>CDM, CO2</h1>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h5>Ukupno smanjenje emisije CO2 tokom 20 godina, koji se odnosi na projektovani radni vek vetroelektrane iznosio bi 5,4 miliona tona CO2. Proračun smanjenja emisije CO2 urađen je prema primenjivoj metodologiji za ocenu projekta mehanizma čistog razvoja (CDM).\r\n\r\nTipično putničko vozilo emituje oko 5,1 tonu CO2 godišnje. Doprinos iz zelene energije dobijene iz vetra u vetroelektrani „Plandište 1“ bi bila ekvivalentna ukljanjanju 53 000 automobila sa ulica svake godine.\r\n\r\nProjekat vetroelektrana „Plandište 1“ odobren je kao projekat Mehanizma čistog razvoja od Nacionalnog tela za sproveđenje projekata mehanizama čistog razvoja, Ministarstvo životne sredine, rudarstva i prostornog planiranja.\r\n\r\nTakođe, projekat je prihvaćen kao projekat mehanizma čistog razvoja od strane Konferencije država ugovornica okvirne konvencije ujedinjenih nacija o promeni klime</h5>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a></div><!--:--><!--:en--><h1>CDM, CO2</h1>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h5>The total reduction of CO2 emission over 20 years, related to the projected life of the wind parks would be 5.4 million tons of CO2. The calculation of reduction of CO2 emission was made according to the applicable methodology for assessment of the clean development mechanism (CDM) project.\r\n\r\nA typical passenger vehicle emits about 5.1 ton of CO2 annually. The contribution from green energy obtained from the wind at the “Plandište 1“ wind park would be equivalent to removal of 53 000 cars from the street every year.\r\n\r\nThe “Plandište 1“ wind park was approved as a Clean Development Mechanism project by the National Authority for the implementation of clean development mechanism project, Ministry of Environment, Mining and Spatial Planning.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the project was approved as a clean development mechanism project by the Conference of Parties on United National Framework Convention on Climate Change</h5>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a></div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->CDM, CO2<!--:--><!--:en-->CDM, CO2<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 14:36:44', '2014-02-01 13:36:44', '', 36, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=37', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
