(54, 1, '2014-02-01 14:41:48', '2014-02-01 13:41:48', '<!--:SR-->Projekti izgradnje vetroenergetskih postrojenja predstavljaju veliki doprinos očuvanju životne sredine na svim nivoima, od lokanog do globalnog. Njihov negativan uticaj na prirodnu sredinu i životnu zajednicu je neznatan i skoro zanemarljiv (uz upotrebu mera prevencije, smanjenja ili otklanjanja negativnih uticaja).\r\n\r\nSvrha projekta vetroelektrane „Plandište 1“ je proizvodnja zelene energije kroz izgradnju i rad vetroturbina ukupne instalisane snage do 102 MW.\r\n\r\nPotreba izrade Studije procene uticaja projekta Izgradnja energetskog objekta za proizvodnju električne energije vetroelektrana „Plandište 1“ na životnu sredinu izražena je i rešenjem Pokrajinskog sekretarijata za urbanizam, graditeljstvo i zaštitu životne sredine, Autonomne Pokrajine Vojvodina, Rešenje broj: 130-501-1151/2011-06 od 07.07.2011. godine. Ovim rešenjem definisan je i obim i sadržaj studije, odnosno potreba da se procena uradi u skladu sa Pravilnikom o sadržini studije o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu („Sl. glasnik RS“, br. 69/05).\r\n\r\nStudija o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu urađena je od strane privrednog društva „Dekonta“ d.o.o., Beograd, sa osnovnim ciljem da se analizira problematika uticaja planiranog Projekta na životnu sredinu. Na osnovu ove studije, 13.06.2012. godine, dobijeno je Rešenje (broj: 130-501-840/2012-06) o davanju saglasnosti na Studiju o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu, od strane Pokrajinskog sekretarijata za urbanizam, graditeljstvo i zaštitu životne sredine. Ovim rešenjem se potvrđuje da je Studija o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu izrađena u svemu prema utvrđenim normativima koji su propisani Zakonom o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu („Službeni glasnik RS“, br. 135/04).\r\n\r\nPrilikom izrade studije o proceni uticaja zatečenog stanja korišćene su sledeće podloge:\r\n- Zakonska regulativa\r\n- Tehnička dokumentacija\r\n\r\nMonitoring faune ptica i slepih miševa izvršen je u trajanju od godinu dana. Registrovano je prisustvo 107 vrsta ptica, od kojih je većina bila u niskoj brojnosti, što je posledica jednoličnosti i prisustva neoptimalnih staništa, kao i prisustvo 12 vrsta slepih miševa strogo zaštićenih domaćim zakonom. Iako je konstatovan značajan broj vrsta slepih miševa, najveći deo njih je beležen u relativno malom broju.\r\n\r\nIzgradnja projekta na ovoj lokaciji imaće pozitivan uticaj i na druge regione u Republici Srbiji jer će omogućiti elektranama koje snabdevaju električnom energijom ovaj region da preusmere svoje kapacitete bližim korisnicima i potrošačima. Ovo će rezultovati manjim gubicima energije, koji se javljaju kao posledica prenosa energije na veće daljine, i boljoj energetskoj efikasnosti drugih elektrana.<!--:--><!--:en-->The wind park development projects are a major contribution to preserving the environment at all levels, from the local to the global. Their negative impact on the natural environment and living community is insignificant and almost negligible (with the implementation of measures for prevention, reduction or elimination of negative impacts).\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the “Plandište 1“ wind park is production of green energy through construction and operation of wind turbines with total installed power of 102 MW.\r\n\r\nThe need to prepare the Environmental Impact Assessment Study for the project of Construction of power facility for production of electricity “Plandište 1“ wind park is also presented by the resolution of the Provincial Secretariat for Town Planning, Civil Engineering and Environmental Protection, of the Autonomous Province of Vojvodina, Resolution No.: 130-501-1151/2011-06 dated 7/7/2011. This Resolution stipulates the scope and purport of the study, namely, the need to make an assessment in compliance with the Rules of Procedure on the purport of the study of assessment of environmental impact (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No.. 69/05).\r\n\r\nThe Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared by the company “Dekonta“ d.o.o., Belgrade, with the main goal of analyzing the issue of environmental impact of the planned Project. On 13/6/2012, based on this Study, a Resolution (No: 130-501-840/2012-06) was obtained on granting the approval of the Environmental Impact Assessment Study by the Provincial Secretariat for Town Planning, Civil Engineering and Environmental Protection. This resolution confirmed that the Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared fully in compliance with the set standards prescribed by the Law on Environmental Assessment (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No. 135/04).\r\n\r\nThe following basic data were used in preparing the impact assessment Study on the as-found state:\r\n- Regulatory rules\r\n- Technical documentation\r\n\r\nMonitoring of fauna, birds and bats was performed over a period of one year. A presence of 107 bird species was registered, most of which had a low count which is a consequence of invariability and presence of non-optimal habitats, as well as 12 species of bats strictly protected by national law. Although a significant number of bats was registered, the greatest part was registered in a relatively small number.\r\n\r\nThe development of the project on this location will also have a positive impact on other regions in the Republic of Serbia and will enable the power plants supplying electricity to this region to redirect their output to closer users and consumers. This will result in smaller energy losses that appear as a consequence of transmission of electricity to greater distances and better energy efficiency of other power plants.<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Studija o proceni uticaja<!--:--><!--:en-->Impact assessment study<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'studija-o-proceni-uticaja', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:32:35', '2014-02-01 16:32:35', '', 0, 'http://nemanja-pc/?page_id=54', 0, 'page', '', 0),
