of the study of assessment of environmental impact (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No.. 69/05).\r\n\r\nThe Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared by the company “Dekonta“ d.o.o., Belgrade, with the main goal of analyzing the issue of environmental impact of the planned Project. On 13/6/2012, based on this Study, a Resolution (No: 130-501-840/2012-06) was obtained on granting the approval of the Environmental Impact Assessment Study by the Provincial Secretariat for Town Planning, Civil Engineering and Environmental Protection. This resolution confirmed that the Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared fully in compliance with the set standards prescribed by the Law on Environmental Assessment (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No. 135/04).\r\n\r\nThe following basic data were used in preparing the impact assessment Study on the as-found state:\r\n- Regulatory rules\r\n- Technical documentation\r\n\r\nMonitoring of fauna, birds and bats was performed over a period of one year. A presence of 107 bird species was registered, most of which had a low count which is a consequence of invariability and presence of non-optimal habitats, as well as 12 species of bats strictly protected by national law. Although a significant number of bats was registered, the greatest part was registered in a relatively small number.\r\n\r\nThe development of the project on this location will also have a positive impact on other regions in the Republic of Serbia and will enable the power plants supplying electricity to this region to redirect their output to closer users and consumers. This will result in smaller energy losses that appear as a consequence of transmission of electricity to greater distances and better energy efficiency of other power plants.</h5>\r\n</div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Studija o proceni uticaja<!--:--><!--:en-->Impact assessment study<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 14:41: