čka struktura<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:24:10', '2014-02-01 16:24:10', '', 15, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=62', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(63, 1, '2014-02-01 17:24:58', '2014-02-01 16:24:58', '<!--:SR-->Vlasnička struktura\r\n\r\nKompanija NIS Energowind doo je 2010. godine osnovala svoje zavisno društvo, kompaniju <b>Wind Park Plandište doo</b>, kao kompaniju koja će biti nosilac projekta izgradnje vetroelektrane „Plandište 1“ na teritoriji opštine Plandište. Planirano je da se ovaj projekat sastoji od 34 vetrogeneratora, ukupne instalisane snage 102 MW. 50% vlasništva kompanije je posredno u rukama kompanije NIS, a preostalih 50% je u vlasništvu privatnih investitora.\r\n\r\n<b>NIS</b> je jedna od najvećih vertikalno integrisanih kompanija u jugoistočnoj Evropi. Osnovne delatnosti su istraživanja, proizvodnja i prerada nafte i gasa, promet naftnih derivata, kao i realizacija projekata u oblasti petrohemije i energetike. Gazprom Neft poseduje 56,15% akcijskog kapitala NIS-a, dok je 29,88% akcija NIS-a u vlasništvu Republike Srbije. Ostatak pripada građanima, zaposlenima, bivšim zaposlenima i drugim manjinskim akcionarima.<!--:--><!--:en-->PROJECT\r\n\r\nThirty-four state-of-the-art wind power turbines will be constructed within the wind “Plandište 1“ wind park. Total installed power of the facility is 102 MW.\r\n\r\nThe wind park will be connected to the electricity transmission system of the Republic of Serbia through a newly erected transformer station and existing 110 kV low voltage transmission line.\r\n\r\nThe wind park will spread over 4500 ha of agricultural land of the South Banat municipality Plandište.\r\n\r\nWith all of its required building permits, several years of relevant measurement of wind potential on a 125 m tall weather pole, favorably chosen site, the “Plandište 1“ wind park, once executed, will be an important power facility and a significant tourist location in the country.<!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Project<!--:--><!--:SR-->Projekat<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:24:58', '2014-02-01 16:24:58', '', 17, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=63', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(64, 1, '2014-02-01 17:25:48', '2014-02-01 16:25:48', '<!--:SR-->Ukupno smanjenje emisije CO2 tokom 20 godina, koji se odnosi na projektovani radni vek vetroelektrane iznosio bi 5,4 miliona tona CO2. Proračun smanjenja emisije CO2 urađen je prema primenjivoj metodologiji za ocenu projekta mehanizma čistog razvoja (CDM).\r\n\r\nTipično putničko vozilo emituje oko 5,1 tonu CO2 godišnje. Doprinos iz zelene energije dobijene iz vetra u vetroelektrani „Plandište 1“ bi bila ekvivalentna ukljanjanju 53 000 automobila sa ulica svake godine.\r\n\r\nProjekat vetroelektrana „Plandište 1“ odobren je kao projekat Mehanizma čistog razvoja od Nacionalnog tela za sproveđenje projekata mehanizama čistog razvoja, Ministarstvo životne sredine, rudarstva i prostornog planiranja.\r\n\r\nTakođe, projekat je prihvaćen kao projekat mehanizma čistog razvoja od strane Konferencije država ugovornica okvirne konvencije ujedinjenih nacija o promeni klime</h5>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a><!--:--><!--:en-->The total reduction of CO2 emission over 20 years, related to the projected life of the wind parks would be 5.4 million tons of CO2. The calculation of reduction of CO2 emission was made according to the applicable methodology for assessment of the clean development mechanism (CDM) project.\r\n\r\nA typical passenger vehicle emits about 5.1 ton of CO2 annually. The contribution from green energy obtained from the wind at the “Plandište 1“ wind park would be equivalent to removal of 53 000 cars from the street every year.\r\n\r\nThe “Plandište 1“ wind park was approved as a Clean Development Mechanism project by the National Authority for the implementation of clean development mechanism project, Ministry of Environment, Mining and Spatial Planning.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the project was approved as a clean development mechanism project by the Conference of Parties on United National Framework Convention on Climate Change\r\n\r\n<a href="http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html" target="_blank">http://cdm.unfccc.int/Projects/registered.html</a><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->CDM, CO2<!--:--><!--:en-->CDM, CO2<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:25:48', '2014-02-01 16:25:48', '', 36, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=64', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
