(66, 1, '2014-02-01 17:26:31', '2014-02-01 16:26:31', '<!--:SR-->Rešavanje imovinsko-pravnih odnosa\r\n\r\n- Procena potencijala vetra\r\n\r\n- Plan detaljne regulacije\r\n\r\n- Energetska dozvola\r\n\r\n- Lokacijska dozvola\r\n\r\n- Idejni projekat\r\n\r\n- Glavni projekat\r\n\r\n- Građevinska dozvola\r\n\r\n- Izgradnja vetroelektrane i priključenje na mrežu\r\n\r\n- Privremeni status povlašćenog proizvođača el. Energije\r\n\r\n- Preliminarni ugovor o otkupu električne energije\r\n\r\n- Upotrebna dozvola\r\n\r\n- Energetska licenca za obavljanje energetske delatnosti proizvodnje električne energije\r\n\r\n- Status povlašćenog proizvođača električne energije\r\n\r\n- Ugovor o otkupu električne energije<!--:--><!--:en-->Resolving the property relations\r\n\r\n- Assessment of wind potential\r\n\r\n- Detailed regulation plan\r\n\r\n- Energy permit\r\n\r\n- Location permit\r\n\r\n- Conceptual design\r\n\r\n- Main design\r\n\r\n- Building permit\r\n\r\n- Construction of wind park and connection to the grid\r\n\r\n- Temporary status of preferential electric power producer\r\n\r\n- Preliminary electric power purchase agreement\r\n\r\n- Inspection certificate\r\n\r\n- Energy license for renewable energy activity of electric power production\r\n\r\n- Status of preferential electric power producer\r\n\r\n- Power purchase agreement<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Kako je sve počelo - glavni koraci<!--:--><!--:en-->How did it begin - Main steps in project development<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:26:31', '2014-02-01 16:26:31', '', 28, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=66', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(67, 1, '2014-02-01 17:27:40', '2014-02-01 16:27:40', '<!--:SR-->Ratifikacijom Ugovora o osnivanju energetske zajednice između EU i zemalja Jugoistočne Evrope, Republika Srbija je prihvatila obavezu da donese i realizuje plan primene direktive 2001/77/EC i 2003/30/EC o promovisanju proizvodnje električne energije iz obnovljivih izvora i smanjenju emisije gasova koji zagađuju životnu sredinu. Tokom 2009. godine Evropski parlament i Savet Evropske unije usvojili su Direktivu 2009/28/EC o promovisanju upotrebe energije iz obnovljivih izvora i poništili Direktivu 2001/77/EC i 2003/30/EC.\r\n\r\nŠto se Srbije tiče, Radna grupa Energetske zajednice Jugoistočne Evrope usaglasila je da je udeo energije iz obnovljivih izvora u Srbiji u 2009. god. iznosio 21,2% u bruto finalnoj potrošnji energije.\r\n\r\nOvo predstavlja osnovu za utvrđivanje udela obnovljivih izvora koji Srbija, u skladu sa evropskim ciljevima, treba da ostvari do 2020. Godine, a koji iznosi 27% bruto finalne potrošnje.\r\n\r\nOvo poboljšanje energetske budućnosti je neophodno kako bi Srbija doprinela svetskoj borbi protiv klimatskih promena.\r\n\r\nU tom cilju, nadležne institucije u Srbiji ustanovili su regulativu koja bi omogućila investicije u obnovljive izvore energije, između ostalog i vetar. Pogodna regulativa za razvoj projekata obnovljivih izvora energije igra veliku ulogu u privlačenju potrebnih stranih ulaganja i otvaranja radnih mesta u opštinama u kojima su projekti locirani.\r\n\r\nZakon o energetici i prateća regulativa prepoznaje značaj obnovljivih izvora energije. Međutim, kako bi se veliki projekti poput vetroelektrana realizovali, neophodno je da se donesu određene izmene samog zakona, a čije donošenje se očekuje krajem 2013. godine.\r\n\r\nUsvojen su i četiri bitne Uredbe (podzakonski akti) koje čine osnovu okvira podsticajnih mera za projekte obnovljivih izvora energije:\r\n• Uredba o uslovima i postupku sticanja statusa povlašćenog proizvođača električne energije (Sl. glasnik RS, br. 8/2013),\r\n• Uredba o merama podsticaja za povlašćene proizvođače električne energije (Sl. glasnik RS, br. 8/2013),\r\n• Uredba o načinu obračuna i načinu raspodele prikupljenih sredstava po osnovu naknade za podsticaj povlašćenih proizvođača električne energije (Sl. glasnik RS, br. 8/2013),\r\n• Uredba o visini posebne naknade za podsticaj u 2013. godini (Sl. glasnik RS, br. 8/2013).\r\n\r\nDa bi zakonski okvir bio potpuno zatvoren nedostaje odgovarajući Ugovor o otkupu električne energije (PPA), koji je neophodan kako bi se omogućilo finansiranje projekata. Sadašnja verzija ovog ugovora ne zadovoljava zahteve banaka i finansijskih institucija. Usvajanje odgovarajuće verzije Ugovora se očekuje početkom 2014. godine.\r\n\r\n26. januara 2009. godine Republika Srbija je postala članica i osnivač Međunarodne agencije za obnovljivu energiju (IRENA- International Renewable Energy Agency), kao prve međunarodne organizacije koja se fokusira isključivo na obnovljivu energiju i aktivno će nastaviti učešće u radu ove agencije u skladu sa Statutom Agencije i svojim interesima u oblasti aktiviranja i korišćenja obnovljivih izvora energije.<!--:--><!--:en-->With the ratification of the Treaty establishing the Energy Community between EU and South East European countries, the Republic of Serbia accepted the obligation to pass and execute the plan of implementation of Directive 2001/77/EC and 2003/30/EC on the promotion of production of electricity from renewable energy sources and reduction of gas emissions polluting the environment. In the course of 2009 the European Parliament and the European Union Council passed the Directive 2009/28/EC on the promotion of the use of energy from renewable sources and repealing of Directives 2001/77/EC and 2003/30/EC.\r\n\r\nAs for Serbia, the Task Force of the Energy Community of Southeast Europe determined that the share of energy from renewable sources in Serbia in 2009 makes 21.2% of the gross final energy consumption.\r\n\r\nThis served as a basis for determining the share of renewable sources that Serbia is to realize by 2020 in accordance with the European targets, which makes 27% of the gross final consumption.\r\n\r\nSuch improvement of the energy future is essential in order for Serbia to contribute to the global struggle against climate changes.\r\n\r\nThe competent institutions in Serbia have established for this purpose a subregulation that would enable investments in renewable energy sources, the wind among others. A convenient regulation for the development of renewable energy sources projects plays a major role in attracting the required foreign investments and opening up of jobs in the municipalities in which the projects are situated.\r\n\r\nThe Energy Law and the accompanying regulations recognize the importance of renewable energy sources. However, in order to realize the major projects such as wind parks, it is necessary to make certain amendments to the Law, which is expected to be passed by the end of 2013.\r\n\r\nFour essential Decrees (bylaws) have been passed which form the basis of the framework of incentive measures for the projects of renewable energy sources:\r\n• Decree on conditions and procedures for attaining the status of preferential electric power producer (Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia No. 8/2013),\r\n• Decree on incentive measures for preferential electric power producers (Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia No. 8/2013),\r\n• Decree on the manner of accounting and allocation of collected assets based on remuneration for stimulation of electric power producers (Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia No. 8/2013),\r\n• Decree on special remuneration tariffs for incentive in 2013 (Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia No. 8/2013).\r\nFor a legal framework to be fully complete, a respective Power Purchase Agreement (PPA), which is necessary to facilitate project financing, is missing. The current version of this agreement does not meet the requirements of banks and financial institutions. The adoption of the respective version of the Agreement is expected in early 2014.\r\n\r\nOn January 26, 2009 the Republic of Serbia became a member and founder of the International Renewable Energy Agency (IRENA), as the first international organizations focused solely on renewable energy and will continue active participation in the work of this agency in accordance with the Agency Statute and its interests in the domain of activation and use of renewable energy sources.<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Kako je sve počelo - zakonska regulativa<!--:--><!--:en-->How did it begin - Regulatory rules<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '26-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:27:40', '2014-02-01 16:27:40', '', 26, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=67', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(68, 1, '2014-02-01 17:28:04', '2014-02-01 16:28:04', '<!--:SR-->Kompanija NIS Energowind doo je 2010. godine osnovala svoje zavisno društvo, kompaniju <b>Wind Park Plandište doo</b>, kao kompaniju koja će biti nosilac projekta izgradnje vetroelektrane „Plandište 1“ na teritoriji opštine Plandište. Planirano je da se ovaj projekat sastoji od 34 vetrogeneratora, ukupne instalisane snage 102 MW. 50% vlasništva kompanije je posredno u rukama kompanije NIS, a preostalih 50% je u vlasništvu privatnih investitora.\r\n<b>NIS</b> je jedna od najvećih vertikalno integrisanih kompanija u jugoistočnoj Evropi. Osnovne delatnosti su istraživanja, proizvodnja i prerada nafte i gasa, promet naftnih derivata, kao i realizacija projekata u oblasti petrohemije i energetike. Gazprom Neft poseduje 56,15% akcijskog kapitala NIS-a, dok je 29,88% akcija NIS-a u vlasništvu Republike Srbije. Ostatak pripada građanima, zaposlenima, bivšim zaposlenima i drugim manjinskim akcionarima.<!--:--><!--:en-->In 2010 NIS Energowind doo founded its subsidiary company, <b>Wind Park Plandište doo</b>, as leader of the project of construction of “Plandište 1“ wind park on the territory of the municipality Plandište. This project is planned to include 34 wind turbines, total installed power of 102 MW. Fifty percent of the Company ownership is indirectly held by NIS company, and the remaining 50% is owned by private investors.\r\n<b>NIS</b> is one of the largest vertically integrated companies in Southeast Europe. The core activities are research, production and processing of oil and gas, trade in oil derivatives as well as execution of projects in the field of petrochemistry and energy. Gazprom Neft holds 56.15% of NIS share capital, whereas 29.88% of NIS shares is held by the Republic of Serbia. The rest belongs to the citizens, employees, former employees and other minority shareholders.<!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Ownership structure<!--:--><!--:SR-->Vlasnička struktura<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:28:04', '2014-02-01 16:28:04', '', 15, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=68', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(69, 1, '2014-02-01 17:28:30', '2014-02-01 16:28:30', '<!--:SR-->Kompanija NIS Energowind doo je 2010. godine osnovala svoje zavisno društvo, kompaniju <b>Wind Park Plandište doo</b>, kao kompaniju koja će biti nosilac projekta izgradnje vetroelektrane „Plandište 1“ na teritoriji opštine Plandište. Planirano je da se ovaj projekat sastoji od 34 vetrogeneratora, ukupne instalisane snage 102 MW. 50% vlasništva kompanije je posredno u rukama kompanije NIS, a preostalih 50% je u vlasništvu privatnih investitora.\r\n\r\n<b>NIS</b> je jedna od najvećih vertikalno integrisanih kompanija u jugoistočnoj Evropi. Osnovne delatnosti su istraživanja, proizvodnja i prerada nafte i gasa, promet naftnih derivata, kao i realizacija projekata u oblasti petrohemije i energetike. Gazprom Neft poseduje 56,15% akcijskog kapitala NIS-a, dok je 29,88% akcija NIS-a u vlasništvu Republike Srbije. Ostatak pripada građanima, zaposlenima, bivšim zaposlenima i drugim manjinskim akcionarima.<!--:--><!--:en-->Thirty-four state-of-the-art wind power turbines will be constructed within the wind “Plandište 1“ wind park. Total installed power of the facility is 102 MW.\r\n\r\nThe wind park will be connected to the electricity transmission system of the Republic of Serbia through a newly erected transformer station and existing 110 kV low voltage transmission line.\r\n\r\nThe wind park will spread over 4500 ha of agricultural land of the South Banat municipality Plandište.\r\n\r\nWith all of its required building permits, several years of relevant measurement of wind potential on a 125 m tall weather pole, favorably chosen site, the “Plandište 1“ wind park, once executed, will be an important power facility and a significant tourist location in the country.<!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Project<!--:--><!--:SR-->Projekat<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:28:30', '2014-02-01 16:28:30', '', 17, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=69', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(70, 1, '2014-02-01 17:30:04', '2014-02-01 16:30:04', '<!--:SR--><b>NIS Energowind doo</b> je kompanija koja u Srbiji postoji više od osam godina i predstavlja ozbiljnog investitora i promotera na polju obnovljivih izvora energije. Članica je SEWEA (Serbian Wind Energy Association) asocijacije.\r\n\r\nGlavni cilj kompanije je razvoj, izgradnja i upravljanje vetroelektranama u Srbiji, kao i prodaja proizvedene električne energije „EPS Snabdevanju“ i/ili drugim kompanijama.\r\n\r\nOstali ciljevi kompanije su:\r\n\r\n• Povećanje proizvodnje električne energije iz obnovljivih izvora korišćenjem novih tehnologija;\r\n• Efikasna upotreba postojeće energetske i komunalne infrastrukture kao i razvoj nove infrastrukture;\r\n• Ekonomska podrška lokalnim zajednicama kroz poboljšanje infrastrukture, upošljavanje lokalnog stanovništva tokom gradnje itd.\r\n• Zaštita životne sredine i smanjenje emisije CO2.<!--:--><!--:en--><div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>ABOUT US</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><b>NIS Energowind doo</b> is a company existing in Serbia over eight years as a serious investor and promoter in the area of renewable sources of energy. It is a member of SEWEA (Serbian Wind Energy Association).\r\n\r\nThe Company’s main target is development, construction and management of wind parks in Serbia, as well as sale of produced electricity to „EPS Snabdevanje“ and/or other companies.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>The other company targets are:\r\n\r\n• Enhancement of electric power production from renewable sources using new technologies;\r\n• Efficient use of existing energy and communal infrastructure as well as development of new infrastructure;\r\n• Economic support to local communities by improvement of infrastructure, employment of local population during the construction, etc.\r\n• Environmental protection and CO2 emission.</div>\r\n</div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->O nama<!--:--><!--:en-->About us<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:30:04', '2014-02-01 16:30:04', '', 13, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=70', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(71, 1, '2014-02-01 17:30:25', '2014-02-01 16:30:25', '<!--:SR--><b>NIS Energowind doo</b> je kompanija koja u Srbiji postoji više od osam godina i predstavlja ozbiljnog investitora i promotera na polju obnovljivih izvora energije. Članica je SEWEA (Serbian Wind Energy Association) asocijacije.\r\n\r\nGlavni cilj kompanije je razvoj, izgradnja i upravljanje vetroelektranama u Srbiji, kao i prodaja proizvedene električne energije „EPS Snabdevanju“ i/ili drugim kompanijama.\r\n\r\nOstali ciljevi kompanije su:\r\n\r\n• Povećanje proizvodnje električne energije iz obnovljivih izvora korišćenjem novih tehnologija;\r\n• Efikasna upotreba postojeće energetske i komunalne infrastrukture kao i razvoj nove infrastrukture;\r\n• Ekonomska podrška lokalnim zajednicama kroz poboljšanje infrastrukture, upošljavanje lokalnog stanovništva tokom gradnje itd.\r\n• Zaštita životne sredine i smanjenje emisije CO2.<!--:--><!--:en--><b>NIS Energowind doo</b> is a company existing in Serbia over eight years as a serious investor and promoter in the area of renewable sources of energy. It is a member of SEWEA (Serbian Wind Energy Association).\r\n\r\nThe Company’s main target is development, construction and management of wind parks in Serbia, as well as sale of produced electricity to „EPS Snabdevanje“ and/or other companies.\r\n\r\nThe other company targets are:\r\n\r\n• Enhancement of electric power production from renewable sources using new technologies;\r\n• Efficient use of existing energy and communal infrastructure as well as development of new infrastructure;\r\n• Economic support to local communities by improvement of infrastructure, employment of local population during the construction, etc.\r\n• Environmental protection and CO2 emission.<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->O nama<!--:--><!--:en-->About us<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:30:25', '2014-02-01 16:30:25', '', 13, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=71', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2014-02-01 17:30:57', '2014-02-01 16:30:57', '<!--:SR--><h1></h1><!--:--><!--:en-->The “Plandište 1” wind park is located in the northeast of Serbia, in Southern Banat, well known for the strong wind called “Košava”. The main direction of the Košave is southeast – northwest. The average wind velocity on the location (at the level of 125 m) is above 6.5 m/s, with minimum turbulence intensity.\r\n\r\nThe unevenness of the grounds is such that it is very favorable for using the wind energy. The measurement of wind characteristics has been performed on the site on a 125 m high weather pole for several years. The pole is furnished with highest class sensor, placed at the respective heights. The measurements have been performed since April 2011.\r\n\r\nThe GMAO MERRA (Global Modeling and Assimilation Office of the NASA Centre for Climate Simulation – The Modern Era Retrospective-analysis for Research and Applications) data were used for the long-term correlation of wind related data.\r\n\r\nThe wind potential analyses and the annual return for various producers and models of wind turbines were prepared by two independent globally recognized consulting companies (DEWI and Anemos GmbH).<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Opis projekta - Analiza potencijala vetra<!--:--><!--:en-->Project description - Analysis of the wind potential<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:30:57', '2014-02-01 16:30:57', '', 32, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=72', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2014-02-01 17:31:07', '2014-02-01 16:31:07', '<!--:en-->The “Plandište 1” wind park is located in the northeast of Serbia, in Southern Banat, well known for the strong wind called “Košava”. The main direction of the Košave is southeast – northwest. The average wind velocity on the location (at the level of 125 m) is above 6.5 m/s, with minimum turbulence intensity.\r\n\r\nThe unevenness of the grounds is such that it is very favorable for using the wind energy. The measurement of wind characteristics has been performed on the site on a 125 m high weather pole for several years. The pole is furnished with highest class sensor, placed at the respective heights. The measurements have been performed since April 2011.\r\n\r\nThe GMAO MERRA (Global Modeling and Assimilation Office of the NASA Centre for Climate Simulation – The Modern Era Retrospective-analysis for Research and Applications) data were used for the long-term correlation of wind related data.\r\n\r\nThe wind potential analyses and the annual return for various producers and models of wind turbines were prepared by two independent globally recognized consulting companies (DEWI and Anemos GmbH).<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Opis projekta - Analiza potencijala vetra<!--:--><!--:en-->Project description - Analysis of the wind potential<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:31:07', '2014-02-01 16:31:07', '', 32, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=73', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2014-02-01 17:31:45', '2014-02-01 16:31:45', '<!--:SR-->Opština Plandište se nalazi u severnoj pokrajini Srbije, Vojvodini, na 65 km severoistočno od Beograda, 22 km severozapadno od Vršca i na 10 km udaljenosti od granice sa Rumunijom.\r\n\r\nLokacija vetroelekrane Plandište 1 se prostire na oko 4500 hektara i nalazi se između četiri banatska mesta: Plandište, Velika Greda, Jermenovci i Barice.\r\n\r\nTeren na kom će biti postavljeni vetrogeneratori je pretežno ravan, sa nadmorskom visinom koja varira od 74 m do 78 m. Zemljište na lokaciji pretežno ima namenu u poljoprivredi, a najćešće uzgajane kulture su kukuruz, suncokret i žitarice.\r\n\r\nDobra infrastruktura puteva, blizina reke Dunav i plovnog kanala Dunav-Tisa-Dunav, železnička pruga i dalekovod naponskog nivoa 110 kV čine lokaciju vrlo povoljnom za realizaciju projekta vetroelektrane.<!--:--><!--:en-->Municipality Plandište is located in the northern province of Serbia, Vojvodina, 65 km northeast from Belgrade, 22 km northwest from Vršac and 10 km from the border with Romania.\r\n\r\nThe location of the Plandište 1 wind park covers an area of about 4500 hectares and is located between four Banat towns: Plandište, Velika Greda, Jermenovci and Barice.\r\n\r\nThe grounds on which the wind turbines will be placed is mostly flat, with height above sea level varying from 74 m to 78 m. The land on the location is mostly intended for agriculture, and the most frequently grown crops are maize, sunflower and grains.\r\n\r\nA good road infrastructure, vicinity of the Danube river and the navigable canal Dunav-Tisa-Dunav, railway line and 110 kV low voltage transmission line make this location highly favorable for the execution of the wind park project.<!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Opis projekta - Lokacija<!--:--><!--:en-->Project description - Location<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '30-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:31:45', '2014-02-01 16:31:45', '', 30, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=74', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(75, 1, '2014-02-01 17:32:18', '2014-02-01 16:32:18', '<!--:SR-->Projekti izgradnje vetroenergetskih postrojenja predstavljaju veliki doprinos očuvanju životne sredine na svim nivoima, od lokanog do globalnog. Njihov negativan uticaj na prirodnu sredinu i životnu zajednicu je neznatan i skoro zanemarljiv (uz upotrebu mera prevencije, smanjenja ili otklanjanja negativnih uticaja).\r\n\r\nSvrha projekta vetroelektrane „Plandište 1“ je proizvodnja zelene energije kroz izgradnju i rad vetroturbina ukupne instalisane snage do 102 MW.\r\n\r\nPotreba izrade Studije procene uticaja projekta Izgradnja energetskog objekta za proizvodnju električne energije vetroelektrana „Plandište 1“ na životnu sredinu izražena je i rešenjem Pokrajinskog sekretarijata za urbanizam, graditeljstvo i zaštitu životne sredine, Autonomne Pokrajine Vojvodina, Rešenje broj: 130-501-1151/2011-06 od 07.07.2011. godine. Ovim rešenjem definisan je i obim i sadržaj studije, odnosno potreba da se procena uradi u skladu sa Pravilnikom o sadržini studije o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu („Sl. glasnik RS“, br. 69/05).\r\n\r\nStudija o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu urađena je od strane privrednog društva „Dekonta“ d.o.o., Beograd, sa osnovnim ciljem da se analizira problematika uticaja planiranog Projekta na životnu sredinu. Na osnovu ove studije, 13.06.2012. godine, dobijeno je Rešenje (broj: 130-501-840/2012-06) o davanju saglasnosti na Studiju o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu, od strane Pokrajinskog sekretarijata za urbanizam, graditeljstvo i zaštitu životne sredine. Ovim rešenjem se potvrđuje da je Studija o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu izrađena u svemu prema utvrđenim normativima koji su propisani Zakonom o proceni uticaja na životnu sredinu („Službeni glasnik RS“, br. 135/04).\r\n\r\nPrilikom izrade studije o proceni uticaja zatečenog stanja korišćene su sledeće podloge:\r\n- Zakonska regulativa\r\n- Tehnička dokumentacija\r\n\r\nMonitoring faune ptica i slepih miševa izvršen je u trajanju od godinu dana. Registrovano je prisustvo 107 vrsta ptica, od kojih je većina bila u niskoj brojnosti, što je posledica jednoličnosti i prisustva neoptimalnih staništa, kao i prisustvo 12 vrsta slepih miševa strogo zaštićenih domaćim zakonom. Iako je konstatovan značajan broj vrsta slepih miševa, najveći deo njih je beležen u relativno malom broju.\r\n\r\nIzgradnja projekta na ovoj lokaciji imaće pozitivan uticaj i na druge regione u Republici Srbiji jer će omogućiti elektranama koje snabdevaju električnom energijom ovaj region da preusmere svoje kapacitete bližim korisnicima i potrošačima. Ovo će rezultovati manjim gubicima energije, koji se javljaju kao posledica prenosa energije na veće daljine, i boljoj energetskoj efikasnosti drugih elektrana.<!--:--><!--:en--><h1>Impact assessment study</h1>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h5>The wind park development projects are a major contribution to preserving the environment at all levels, from the local to the global. Their negative impact on the natural environment and living community is insignificant and almost negligible (with the implementation of measures for prevention, reduction or elimination of negative impacts).\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the “Plandište 1“ wind park is production of green energy through construction and operation of wind turbines with total installed power of 102 MW.\r\n\r\nThe need to prepare the Environmental Impact Assessment Study for the project of Construction of power facility for production of electricity “Plandište 1“ wind park is also presented by the resolution of the Provincial Secretariat for Town Planning, Civil Engineering and Environmental Protection, of the Autonomous Province of Vojvodina, Resolution No.: 130-501-1151/2011-06 dated 7/7/2011. This Resolution stipulates the scope and purport of the study, namely, the need to make an assessment in compliance with the Rules of Procedure on the purport of the study of assessment of environmental impact (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No.. 69/05).\r\n\r\nThe Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared by the company “Dekonta“ d.o.o., Belgrade, with the main goal of analyzing the issue of environmental impact of the planned Project. On 13/6/2012, based on this Study, a Resolution (No: 130-501-840/2012-06) was obtained on granting the approval of the Environmental Impact Assessment Study by the Provincial Secretariat for Town Planning, Civil Engineering and Environmental Protection. This resolution confirmed that the Environmental Impact Assessment Study was prepared fully in compliance with the set standards prescribed by the Law on Environmental Assessment (“Official Gazette of the Republic of Serbia” No. 135/04).\r\n\r\nThe following basic data were used in preparing the impact assessment Study on the as-found state:\r\n- Regulatory rules\r\n- Technical documentation\r\n\r\nMonitoring of fauna, birds and bats was performed over a period of one year. A presence of 107 bird species was registered, most of which had a low count which is a consequence of invariability and presence of non-optimal habitats, as well as 12 species of bats strictly protected by national law. Although a significant number of bats was registered, the greatest part was registered in a relatively small number.\r\n\r\nThe development of the project on this location will also have a positive impact on other regions in the Republic of Serbia and will enable the power plants supplying electricity to this region to redirect their output to closer users and consumers. This will result in smaller energy losses that appear as a consequence of transmission of electricity to greater distances and better energy efficiency of other power plants.</h5>\r\n</div><!--:-->', '<!--:SR-->Studija o proceni uticaja<!--:--><!--:en-->Impact assessment study<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '54-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-01 17:32:18', '2014-02-01 16:32:18', '', 54, 'http://nemanja-pc/?p=75', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
